trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of key/value pairs that are sorted on the key.
trans-unit.target: 表示根据键进行排序的键/值对的集合。

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602> generic class is a binary search tree with O(log `n`) retrieval, where `n` is the number of elements in the dictionary.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>泛型类是与 O 二进制搜索树 (日志`n`) 检索，其中`n`是字典中的元素数。

trans-unit.source: In this respect, it is similar to the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> generic class.
trans-unit.target: 在这一方面，它是类似于<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>泛型类。

trans-unit.source: The two classes have similar object models, and both have O(log `n`) retrieval.
trans-unit.target: 两个类具有类似的对象模型，并且都具有 O (日志`n`) 检索。

trans-unit.source: Where the two classes differ is in memory use and speed of insertion and removal:
trans-unit.target: 两个类的不同之处是在内存使用和的插入和删除的速度：

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> uses less memory than <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> 使用较少的内存比<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602> has faster insertion and removal operations for unsorted data: O(log `n`) as opposed to O(`n`) for <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602> 更快的插入和删除操作的未排序的数据： O (日志`n`) 而不是 O (`n`) 为<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>。

trans-unit.source: If the list is populated all at once from sorted data, <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> is faster than <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>.
trans-unit.target: 如果从已排序的数据，在一次填充列表<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>比快<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>。

trans-unit.source: Each key/value pair can be retrieved as a <xref:System.Collections.Generic.KeyValuePair%602> structure, or as a <xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry> through the nongeneric <xref:System.Collections.IDictionary> interface.
trans-unit.target: 可以将每个键/值对的形式进行检索<xref:System.Collections.Generic.KeyValuePair%602>结构，或被<xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry>通过非泛型<xref:System.Collections.IDictionary>接口。

trans-unit.source: Keys must be immutable as long as they are used as keys in the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>.
trans-unit.target: 密钥必须是不可变，只要它们是否用作中的键<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>。

trans-unit.source: Every key in a <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602> must be unique.
trans-unit.target: 中的所有键<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>必须是唯一的。

trans-unit.source: A key cannot be `null`, but a value can be, if the value type `TValue` is a reference type.
trans-unit.target: 密钥不能为`null`，但值则可以为，如果类型值`TValue`是引用类型。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602> requires a comparer implementation to perform key comparisons.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602> 需要一个比较器实现，以执行键的比较。

trans-unit.source: You can specify an implementation of the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IComparer%601> generic interface by using a constructor that accepts a `comparer` parameter; if you do not specify an implementation, the default genericcomparer <xref:System.Collections.Generic.Comparer%601.Default%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> is used.

trans-unit.source: If type `TKey` implements the <xref:System.IComparable%601?displayProperty=nameWithType> generic interface, the default comparer uses that implementation.
trans-unit.target: 如果类型`TKey`实现<xref:System.IComparable%601?displayProperty=nameWithType>泛型接口，则默认比较器使用该实现。

trans-unit.source: The dictionary is maintained in a sorted order using an internal tree.

trans-unit.source: Every new element is positioned at the correct sort position, and the tree is adjusted to maintain the sort order whenever an element is removed.
trans-unit.target: 每个新元素都位于正确的排序位置，并对树进行调整以维护排序顺序，只要移除元素。

trans-unit.source: While enumerating, the sort order is maintained.

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 最初，枚举数定位在集合中第一个元素的前面。

trans-unit.source: At this position, the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602.Enumerator.Current%2A> property is undefined.

trans-unit.target: 如果最后一次调用到<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`，<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602.Enumerator.Current%2A>是不确定的。

trans-unit.target: 只要集合保持不变，枚举数就保持有效。

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`for each` in C++, `For Each` in Visual Basic) hides the complexity of enumerators.
trans-unit.target: `foreach` C# 语言的语句 (`for each` c + + 中`For Each`在 Visual Basic 中) 隐藏了枚举数的复杂性。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended, instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: 因此，建议使用 `foreach`，而不是直接操作枚举数。

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: 枚举器可用于读取集合中的数据，但不能用于修改基础集合。

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 最初，枚举数定位在集合中第一个元素的前面。

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> method also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>方法还会枚举器放回此位置。

trans-unit.source: At this position, the <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> property is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 在此位置上，<xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A>属性是不确定。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> method to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 因此，必须调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>方法将枚举数前移到集合，然后再读取的值的第一个元素<xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A>。

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> property returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A>属性返回相同的对象之前<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>或<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>调用。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 将 <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> 设置为下一个元素。

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: 如果<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>越过的末尾的集合，枚举数定位在集合中的最后一个元素的后面和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: 当枚举器位于此位置上，后续调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>还返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果最后一次调用到<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`，<xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A>是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> to the first element of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 若要再次将 <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> 设置为集合的第一个元素，可以调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 并接着调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>。

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 只要集合保持不变，枚举数就保持有效。

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and its behavior is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果对集合进行更改（如添加、修改或删除元素），则枚举数将失效且不可恢复，而且其行为是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 枚举数没有对集合的独占访问权；因此，从头到尾对一个集合进行枚举在本质上不是一个线程安全的过程。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can lock the collection during the entire enumeration.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保枚举过程中的线程安全性，可以在整个枚举过程中锁定集合。

trans-unit.source: To allow the collection to be accessed by multiple threads for reading and writing, you must implement your own synchronization.
trans-unit.target: 若要允许多个线程访问集合以进行读写操作，则必须实现自己的同步。

trans-unit.source: Default implementations of collections in the <xref:System.Collections.Generic?displayProperty=nameWithType> namespace are not synchronized.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic?displayProperty=nameWithType> 命名空间中集合的默认实现是不同步的。

trans-unit.source: Returns an enumerator that iterates through the collection.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个循环访问集合的枚举器。

trans-unit.source: An <see cref="T:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator`1" /> that can be used to iterate through the collection.
trans-unit.target: 可用于循环访问集合的 <see cref="T:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator`1" />。

trans-unit.source: For purposes of enumeration, each item is a <xref:System.Collections.Generic.KeyValuePair%602> structure representing a value and its key.
trans-unit.target: 枚举而言，对于每个项都是<xref:System.Collections.Generic.KeyValuePair%602>结构，它表示一个值和其密钥。

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`for each` in C++, `For Each` Visual Basic) hides the complexity of enumerators.
trans-unit.target: `foreach` C# 语言的语句 (`for each` c + + 中`For Each`Visual Basic) 隐藏了枚举数的复杂性。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended, instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: 因此，建议使用 `foreach`，而不是直接操作枚举数。

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: 枚举器可用于读取集合中的数据，但不能用于修改基础集合。

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 最初，枚举数定位在集合中第一个元素的前面。

trans-unit.source: At this position, the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> property is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 在此位置上，<xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A>属性是不确定。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> method to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 因此，必须调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>方法将枚举数前移到集合，然后再读取的值的第一个元素<xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A>。

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> property returns the same element until the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> method is called.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A>属性返回之前的相同元素<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>调用方法。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 将 <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> 设置为下一个元素。

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: 如果<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>越过的末尾的集合，枚举数定位在集合中的最后一个元素的后面和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: 当枚举器位于此位置上，后续调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>还返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果最后一次调用到<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`，<xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A>是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: You cannot set <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> to the first element of the collection again; you must create a new enumerator instance instead.
trans-unit.target: 无法再次将 <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> 设置为集合的第一个元素；必须改为创建新的枚举器实例。

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 只要集合保持不变，枚举数就保持有效。

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and its behavior is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果对集合进行更改（如添加、修改或删除元素），则枚举数将失效且不可恢复，而且其行为是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 枚举数没有对集合的独占访问权；因此，从头到尾对一个集合进行枚举在本质上不是一个线程安全的过程。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can lock the collection during the entire enumeration.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保枚举过程中的线程安全性，可以在整个枚举过程中锁定集合。

trans-unit.source: To allow the collection to be accessed by multiple threads for reading and writing, you must implement your own synchronization.
trans-unit.target: 若要允许多个线程访问集合以进行读写操作，则必须实现自己的同步。

trans-unit.source: Default implementations of collections in the <xref:System.Collections.Generic?displayProperty=nameWithType> namespace are not synchronized.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic?displayProperty=nameWithType> 命名空间中集合的默认实现是不同步的。
